        <body>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The following is the entire speech of <persName>MM Noah</persName>,
                delivered<lb/> at the laying of the Corner Stone of the <placeName>City of
                    Ararat</placeName>, to<lb/> be located on <placeName>Grand Island</placeName>.
                It will probably be read with <sic>beco</sic><lb/> interest by all persons feeling a
                desire to acquaint <del>themselves</del><lb/> with the ancient and modern history of
                the Jewish nation.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">SPEECH</p>
            <p>Brothers, Countrymen and Friends</p>
            <p><placeName>N~ Y</placeName> EVNG POST: NUMBER 7241 <date>Saturday September 24,
                    1825</date> No 49 <persName>Williams</persName><lb/> First page begin mid of col
                1 and sev sticks on pg 2</p>
            <p><persName>MAJOR NAOH'S</persName> CITY OF REFUGE FOR THE JEWS</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">A corresp of the <placeName>Rochester</placeName>
                    American;<sic>writing</sic> from<lb/>
                <placeName>Tonawanda</placeName> in this <placeName>State</placeName>, says,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It was here that <persName>Major M M Noah</persName> attempted to
                carry<lb/> out his philanthropic purpose of <sic>fndng</sic> a C of R for his
                scattered<lb/> and <sic>persectd</sic> brethren~ A few rods from the riv there
                stands a little<lb/> brick tower <sic>wh</sic> is fast crumb to ruin, erected by him
                more than a quart of<lb/> a cent ago. In the eastern wall is <sic>palced</sic> a
                stone with a Heb inscript<lb/> and the following in English</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">“<placeName>ARARAT</placeName></p>
            <p rend="align(center)">A CITY OF REFUGE FOR THE JEWS</p>
            <p>Founded by <persName>Mordecai Manasseh Noah</persName>, in the month <date>Tizri,
                    5585</date>.<lb/>
                <date>September, 1825</date>, and in the 50th year of American Independence”</p>
            <p>From <placeName>NEW YORK</placeName> DAY BOOK <date>Aug, 1851</date></p>
            <p>All this on pg 96 Ly S Bk Vol 1</p>
        </body>
